  "error_patterns": "Two recurring patterns beyond the individual errors: (1) m_DELAI applied to S02_INJONCTION records without an actual numeric deadline in the corpus text — Hunter sometimes copied the modifier from the general 'demande formelle' pattern even when the Demande section only says 'dès réception' or references a historical delay already satisfied (4 cases: saft f14, saipol 2023-03-07 f10, saipol 2024-10-31 f08, saipol 2025-09-10 f20). (2) m_MENACE (conditional threat, precursor to M04) was never used across the entire 130-record batch (0 occurrences) despite the corpus containing explicit 'expose l'exploitant à des suites administratives de type mise en demeure' phrasing in at least 5 records (saica f01, saica f09, saipol 2023-03-07 f03, saipol 2023-03-07 f05, saipol 2023-05-16 f05) — Hunter consistently missed this modifier whenever the MED threat was conditional rather than already active. R10_TENSION was not used anywhere in this batch, so the other flagged systematic pattern (R10 misuse for unfulfilled promises) does not apply here. One clear False-M08 case (saipol 252080962024-10-31 f10) had an active 3-month corrective demand on a full-height crack in a retention wall but was tagged as pure conformité — the fiche's own 'CONFORME' label inside the surveillance form appears to have been taken at face value instead of the inspector's follow-up remark requiring further investigation.",
  "verdict": "Hunter output is structurally clean (0/130 STRICT code-validity violations, 0% M15_AUTRE) and the great majority of high-confidence records spot-checked matched the corpus exactly. 15/130 records (11.5%) required correction, in line with the batch's historical <15% error target. Errors cluster around modifier hygiene (m_DELAI without a real deadline, m_MENACE never applied) rather than domain/mechanism selection, plus one genuine False-M08 mis-tag and one mechanism confusion (M14 vs M02 for a manual-vs-continuous measurement gap). All 5 medium-confidence records were individually re-read; 3 of 5 needed correction (mostly stage/mechanism precision), confirming Hunter's confidence flagging was a useful signal of genuine uncertainty."
